text: 158-160 Third Avenue west side between 15th and 16th Street. This property was bought for the estate of Peter Stuyvesant in 1664, and became a part of the Stuyvesant farm. June, 1925.

folder: 3rd Avenue & east side & from 16th to 17th streets., Manhattan, NY
text:
Third Avenue, east side, from 16th to 17th Streets. The building in the centre foreground is the Memorial Chapel of St. George's Protestant Episcopal Church, built in 1888 as a gift of the elder J. Pierpont Morgan. The church itself, a portion of which is seen in this picture, was built in 1849.
July 13, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: 3rd Avenue - east side - from 16th to 17th streets.

text:
Memorial Chapel of St. George's Protestant Episcopal Church, 16th Street adjoining N.E. corner of Third Avenue, seen across clearing at S.E. corner. This building was erected in 1886, the gift of the elder J. Pierpont Morgan. The church itself, a small portion of which is seen at the right, was built in 1849.

July 13, 1929.

P.L. Sperr.
